: 0.997521459992001, \"rank\": 0.0021952992974776492, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France_national_football_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France_national_football_team\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"/CFP  China's He Bingjiao, who claimed the women's singles badminton silver medal at the 2024 Paris Summer Olympics, has retired from international competitions, but will continue to play in domestic matches, the Badminton World Federation (BWF) announced on Tuesday.\", \"from\": 393, \"to\": 660, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 399, \"end\": 404, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China_women's_national_football_team\", \"score\": 0.9949657916799073, \"rank\": 0.004965686797760739, \"text\": \"China\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China_women's_national_football_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China_women's_national_football_team\"}, {\"begin\": 606, \"end\": 632, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Badminton_World_Federation\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Badminton World Federation\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Badminton_World_Federation\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Badminton_World_Federation\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"He Bingjiao faced An Se-young of South Korea in the final at the recently-concluded Games in the French capital.\", \"from\": 662, \"to\": 774, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 695, \"end\": 706, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/South_Korea_national_under-23_football_team\", \"score\": 0.5050571101799212, \"rank\": 0.8101840445151216, \"text\": \"South Korea\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/South_Korea_national_under-23_football_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/South_Korea_national_under-23_football_team\"}, {\"begin\": 759, \"end\": 765, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"score\": 0.783467885608691, \"rank\": 0.27009814760432005, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q315\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Although she lost the gold medal contest, finishing as the runner-up still resulted in her best-ever Olympic performance.\", \"from\": 775, \"to\": 896, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Before Paris 2024, He Bingjiao was a two-time World Championships bronze medalist in the women's singles category and helped China win both the Sudirman Cup and Uber Cup twice.\", \"from\": 898, \"to\": 1074, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 905, \"end\": 915, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2024_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 0.9999999995864073, \"rank\": 4.136668473578968e-10, \"text\": \"Paris 2024\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2024_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2024_Summer_Olympics\"}, {\"begin\": 1023, \"end\": 1028, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China_women's_national_football_team\", \"score\": 0.9949657916799073, \"rank\": 0.004965686797760739, \"text\": \"China\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China_women's_national_football_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China_women's_national_football_team\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"In addition to He Bingjiao's accomplishments as an athlete, she is also widely considered to have a \\\"golden heart\\\" as a person.\", \"from\": 1076, \"to\": 1203, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1091, \"end\": 1102, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/He_Bingjiao\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"He Bingjiao\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/He_Bingjiao\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/He_Bingjiao\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"She advanced to the women's singles final at the 2024 Paris Summer Olympics after her opponent in the semifinals, Carolina Marin of Spain, had to retire from the match after suffering a serious injury.\", \"from\": 1204, \"to\": 1405, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1336, \"end\": 1341, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Spain_national_football_team\", \"score\": 0.997630355323501, \"rank\": 0.0018697613205924388, \"text\": \"Spain\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Spain_national_football_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Spain_national_football_team\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"When He Bingjiao received the silver medal on the podium, she was spotted holding a pin that she said was given to her by the Spanish delegation.\", \"from\": 1407, \"to\": 1552, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1533, \"end\": 1540, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Spanish_language\", \"score\": 0.9740932898350035, \"rank\": 0.025741587386857973, \"text\": \"Spanish\", \"types\": [\"Q315\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Spanish_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Spanish_language\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"This pin was given to me by Team Spain,\\\" He Bingjiao explained at a press conference.\", \"from\": 1554, \"to\": 1640, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1588, \"end\": 1593, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Spain_national_football_team\", \"score\": 0.997630355323501, \"rank\": 0.0018697613205924388, \"text\": \"Spain\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Spain_national_football_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Spain_national_football_team\"}, {\"begin\": 1596, \"end\": 1607, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/He_Bingjiao\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"He Bingjiao\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/He_Bingjiao\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/He_Bingjiao\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"My opponent in the semifinals, Carolina Marin, had to pull out of the match due to injury.\", \"from\": 1641, \"to\": 1732, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1673, \"end\": 1687, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Carolina_Mar\\u00edn\", \"score\": 0.9999990899400066, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Carolina Marin\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Carolina_Mar\\u00edn\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Carolina_Mar\\u00edn\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"I feel sympathetic because Marin is an outstanding athlete and opponent.\", \"from\": 1733, \"to\": 1805, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"I wanted to take her spirit with me to the final.\", \"from\": 1806, \"to\": 1855, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"I wish her a quick recovery.\\\"\", \"from\": 1856, \"to\": 1885, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Both the International Olympic Committee (IOC) and Marin spoke highly of He Bingjiao's act.\", \"from\": 1887, \"to\": 1978, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1896, \"end\": 1933, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"International Olympic Committee (IOC)\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"SITEMAP  EXPLORE MORE  DOWNLOAD OUR APP  Copyright \\u00c2\\u00a9 2024 CGTN.\\u00e4\\u00ba\\u00acICP\\u00e5\\u00a4\\u008720000184\\u00e5\\u008f\\u00b7  Disinformation report hotline: 010-85061466  SITEMAP  EXPLORE MORE  DOWNLOAD OUR APP  Copyright \\u00c2\\u00a9 2024 CGTN.\\u00e4\\u00ba\\u00acICP\\u00e5\\u00a4\\u008720000184\\u00e5\\u008f\\u00b7  Disinformation report hotline: 010-85061466\", \"from\": 1980, \"to\": 2240, \"entities\